textDelta: Moscow Treaty on strategic offensive reductions (SOR) is a treaty between the United States of America and the Soviet Union on the limitation of strategic offensive arms. It was signed on 8 December 1987 and entered into force on 5 June 1990. The treaty was preceded by the Anti-ballistic missile (ABM) Treaty, which prohibited either country from deploying nationwide defenses against strategic ballistic missiles. The treaty was succeeded by the Strategic Offensive Reductions Treaty (SORT). See also Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty References Category:Cold War treaties Category
